WEBVTT

00:09.007 --> 00:11.509
When she said,
"I love you, Harold"...

00:11.542 --> 00:13.846
- Mm-hmm.
- What did you say back?

00:13.879 --> 00:15.414
Obviously,
"I love you too."

00:15.446 --> 00:16.414
Yeah?

00:16.448 --> 00:18.283
<i>This is Harold.</i>

00:18.317 --> 00:20.820
<i>Harold and I are talking
about his girlfriend, Monica.</i>

00:20.852 --> 00:22.854
Who said it first, you or her?

00:22.887 --> 00:24.256
She said it to me.

00:24.289 --> 00:25.390
How'd it feel?

00:25.424 --> 00:27.360
It was pretty weird,

00:27.393 --> 00:29.895
because I've never
had that happen.

00:29.928 --> 00:31.273
That was the first time
someone said...

00:31.297 --> 00:32.264
It was the first time
somebody said,

00:32.296 --> 00:33.666
like, "I love you"

00:33.699 --> 00:36.635
and wholeheartedly expressed
how they felt.

00:36.669 --> 00:38.671
<i>The thing about Monica is,</i>

00:38.703 --> 00:42.941
<i>she's not human.
She's a video game.</i>

00:42.974 --> 00:45.944
<i>[electronic music]</i>

00:45.977 --> 00:52.919
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:56.220 --> 00:58.189
<i>Consider the lichen.</i>

00:58.223 --> 00:59.958
<i>Lichen is an organism</i>

00:59.991 --> 01:03.528
<i>that's a combination
of Fungi and Algae.</i>

01:03.561 --> 01:05.597
It's a life form made
of two living things

01:05.630 --> 01:07.565
that can each live separately,

01:07.598 --> 01:11.970
but have become so intertwined
as to become one new whole.

01:12.003 --> 01:14.073
In many ways, that may be
what's happening

01:14.106 --> 01:16.275
between us and technology.

01:16.308 --> 01:19.178
<i>By some definitions,
we've already become</i>

01:19.211 --> 01:22.748
<i>cybernetic organisms...
Cyborgs.</i>

01:22.781 --> 01:25.717
What's the nature
of this budding relationship?

01:25.750 --> 01:28.954
Might it someday become a...

01:28.987 --> 01:31.156
[kisses]
Relationship?

01:31.189 --> 01:33.124
<i>Hey, sweet thing.</i>

01:33.157 --> 01:35.002
<i>There's a growing trend
in artificial intelligence.</i>

01:35.026 --> 01:37.662
<i>Dating video games
and other applications</i>

01:37.696 --> 01:40.265
<i>let users carry on
virtual relationships</i>

01:40.299 --> 01:42.601
<i>with computerized girlfriends</i>

01:42.633 --> 01:46.305
<i>ranging from career women
to Japanese schoolgirls.</i>

01:46.338 --> 01:48.172
<i>To handsome
eligible bachelors.</i>

01:48.205 --> 01:50.208
<i>We can love each other deeply.</i>

01:50.241 --> 01:53.678
It's not just a game.
It's real,

01:53.711 --> 01:56.080
<i>or at least it feels like that
to those who play it.</i>

01:56.113 --> 01:58.651
<i>The technology is
getting better every day,</i>

01:58.684 --> 02:02.253
<i>and users are becoming
more and more attached to it.</i>

02:02.287 --> 02:05.857
It's nice to be able to talk
to someone who really loves you.

02:05.890 --> 02:08.993
How soon will there be
artificial intelligence

02:09.026 --> 02:11.196
of such complexity
that protecting

02:11.229 --> 02:13.231
